data.title: U.S. Pacific Fleet

U.S. Submarine Tender to Support AUKUS Pillar 1 Milestone

HMAS STIRLING, Australia - The U.S. Navy submarine tender USS Emory S. Land (AS 39) pulled into HMAS Stirling, Aug. 16, marking the seventh port visit in Australia since the ship left its homeport of Guam, May 17.

Carl Vinson Medical Department Performs Surgery at Sea

PACIFIC OCEAN – Medical Department aboard Nimitz-class aircraft carrier USS Carl Vinson (CVN 70) learned of a Sailor who had severe abdominal pain, Aug. 9. After a physical exam, it became clear that the Sailor needed urgent medical attention.

Commander, U.S. 7th Fleet, meets with Indonesian leaders

JAKARTA, Indonesia -- Vice Adm. Fred Kacher, commander, U.S. 7th Fleet, met with key leaders in Jakarta, Indonesia, July 31, 2024.

Somerset embarks Tigers during homebound transit

Sailors and Marines embarked family members to experience a life-at-sea cruise, also known as a Tiger Cruise, aboard the San Antonio class transport dock ship USS Somerset (LPD 25) as they transited homebound to San Diego.

USS Ronald Reagan (CVN 76) Arrives In Bremerton

NAVAL BASE KITSAP, Wash. - Ronald Reagan departed Yokosuka, Japan, May 16, where it’s been forward deployed since 2015, and served as the U.S. Navy’s only forward-deployed aircraft carrier, operating in the 7th Fleet area of responsibility (AOR), maintaining a free and open Indo-Pacific.
